<h1 class="title">Long-term economic growth is biggest factor in lifting people out of poverty</h1>
<p>
In the long run, benefits from increasing the rate of growth will dwarf those from all other actions.
</p>

<p>
For example, the benefits from sustained long term growth over sufficiently long time will become much more important than redistributing wealth at current economic levels. 
</p>

<p>
Trickle down economics obviously works on long time scales.
</p>


